From: stephen hemminger <shemminger@vyatta.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Oct 2012 20:35:47 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 10/39] vxlan: fix byte order in hash function

commit 321fb991399bd7b156f8b15a8acfa0c8622e3c68 upstream.

Shift was wrong direction causing packets to hash based on
other parts of the ethernet header, not the address.

Signed-off-by: Stephen Hemminger <shemminger@vyatta.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
---
 drivers/net/vxlan.c |    4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/vxlan.c b/drivers/net/vxlan.c
index 865c0e9..305d0e8 100644
--- a/drivers/net/vxlan.c
+++ b/drivers/net/vxlan.c
@@ -228,9 +228,9 @@ static u32 eth_hash(const unsigned char *addr)
 
 	/* only want 6 bytes */
 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN
-	value <<= 16;
-#else
 	value >>= 16;
+#else
+	value <<= 16;
 #endif
 	return hash_64(value, FDB_HASH_BITS);
 }
